complaints.summary: Having an issue with my 2014 lexus is350 steering..the steering feels notchy and grabs when going around curves..it does it when returning wheel back to straight position..and wheel has to be pulled back into straight position or it will keep pulling ..thats when it catches and causes the jerk in the steering.. Usually when driving a car It'll somewhat straighten itself smoothly.. I have taken it to repair shops to have alignment/ brakes/rotors done and nothing has helped this what so ever.  I've seen many forums about this same issue.. why hasn't this been addressed ..its obviously a huge issue that's been ignored.. this car isn't old enough or with 89k miles on it to be experiencing these types of issues.. thanks in advance for looking into this!!

issues.title: Carbon Buildup in Direct Injection Engine
issues.description: The 2GR-FSE direct injection engine suffers from carbon buildup on intake valves, causing reduced performance, rough idle, and potential engine damage if left untreated
issues.fix_description: Walnut shell blasting or chemical cleaning of intake valves, typically required every 60,000-80,000 miles
issues.prevention: Use top-tier gasoline, perform regular oil changes, consider periodic induction cleaning services

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing and Black Screen
issues.description: Remote Touch Interface (RTI) system experiences frequent freezing, black screens, and unresponsive touchpad controls
issues.fix_description: Software update or complete head unit replacement depending on severity
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperature changes, keep software updated when available

issues.title: Melting Dashboard
issues.description: Dashboard surface becomes sticky and melts, particularly in hot climates, affecting appearance and potentially releasing harmful chemicals
issues.fix_description: Complete dashboard replacement with updated materials
issues.prevention: Use sunshades, park in shade when possible, apply dashboard protectant

issues.title: Water Pump Failure
issues.description: Premature water pump failure leading to coolant leaks and potential engine overheating
issues.fix_description: Replace water pump and associated gaskets, flush cooling system
issues.prevention: Regular cooling system maintenance, monitor coolant levels, address leaks promptly

issues.title: Steering Rack Failure
issues.description: Electric power steering rack develops internal leaks and binding, causing heavy steering effort and potential loss of steering assist
issues.fix_description: Replace entire steering rack assembly with updated design
issues.prevention: Regular power steering fluid checks, avoid extreme steering inputs

issues.title: Oil Control Valve (VVT-i) Issues
issues.description: Variable Valve Timing oil control valves become clogged or fail, causing timing issues and engine performance problems
issues.fix_description: Clean or replace oil control valves, ensure proper oil viscosity and quality
issues.prevention: Use recommended oil grade, change oil regularly, use quality oil filters

issues.title: Door Handle Paint Peeling
issues.description: Chrome door handle trim experiences paint peeling and corrosion, particularly on models with chrome finish
issues.fix_description: Replace affected door handles or professional refinishing
issues.prevention: Regular washing and waxing, avoid harsh chemicals on handles

issues.title: Brake Actuator Failure
issues.description: ABS/brake actuator unit fails causing loss of power braking assist and potential brake system failure
issues.fix_description: Replace brake actuator assembly, bleed brake system completely
issues.prevention: Regular brake fluid changes, avoid moisture contamination in brake system

issues.title: Transmission Shift Flare
issues.description: 8-speed automatic transmission experiences shift flare and harsh shifting, particularly during 3-4 and 5-6 gear changes
issues.fix_description: Transmission software update or valve body replacement in severe cases
issues.prevention: Regular transmission fluid changes, avoid aggressive driving patterns

issues.title: Spark Plug Coil Pack Failure
issues.description: Ignition coil packs fail prematurely causing misfires and engine performance issues
issues.fix_description: Replace failed coil packs and spark plugs as a set
issues.prevention: Use OEM or high-quality coil packs, replace spark plugs at recommended intervals

issues.title: Sunroof Drain Clogs
issues.description: Sunroof drain tubes become clogged causing water to leak into the cabin and potentially damage electronics
issues.fix_description: Clear drain tubes with compressed air or wire, inspect and repair damaged seals
issues.prevention: Regular sunroof cleaning, keep drain holes clear of debris

editorial.tagline: Naturally aspirated perfection in a refined package
editorial.hero_blurb: The IS350 F Sport delivers pure V6 thrills wrapped in Lexus luxury. This is the thinking enthusiast's sports sedan - sophisticated enough for daily duties yet rewarding when the roads get twisty.
editorial.essence: The IS350 F Sport represents the last of a dying breed - a naturally aspirated V6 in a compact luxury chassis. It combines Lexus refinement with genuine sporting credentials, creating a balanced driver's car that rewards engagement without punishing comfort.
editorial.heritage: Born from Lexus's desire to compete with BMW's 3 Series, the IS line evolved from the Toyota Altezza into a proper luxury sport sedan. The third-generation IS350 refined the formula with sharper handling and more aggressive styling while maintaining the brand's reliability reputation.
editorial.design_philosophy: Form follows function with aggressive F Sport styling cues - deeper air intakes, unique grilles, and sculpted body lines that suggest performance while maintaining Lexus elegance. The interior balances driver focus with luxury appointments.
editorial.motorsport_history: While not directly race-bred, the IS platform has seen action in various touring car championships and serves as the foundation for Lexus's performance development, influencing suspension tuning and aerodynamic refinements.
editorial.engine_character: The 2GR-FSE V6 is a masterpiece of natural aspiration - smooth power delivery from idle to redline with a satisfying crescendo as revs climb. Linear throttle response rewards precise inputs with immediate feedback.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 8-speed automatic is surprisingly engaging in manual mode, with quick downshifts and well-spaced ratios. Sport+ mode holds gears longer and delivers more aggressive shifts that complement spirited driving.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Adaptive Variable Suspension provides excellent body control without harshness. The chassis feels planted and predictable, with just enough compliance to handle real-world road surfaces while maintaining sporting composure.
editorial.steering_feel: Electrically assisted but tuned for feedback - the steering weights up naturally and communicates road surface changes clearly. Quick ratio provides nimble turn-in without being twitchy at highway speeds.
editorial.brake_confidence: Strong, progressive brakes with good pedal feel and minimal fade during spirited driving. The system provides excellent modulation and consistent stopping power that inspires confidence.
editorial.sound_signature: A cultured V6 growl that builds to an angry snarl at high RPM. The exhaust note is sophisticated rather than aggressive - present when you want it, refined when you don't.
editorial.ideal_owner: The discerning enthusiast who values naturally aspirated response, luxury appointments, and proven reliability. Perfect for those who appreciate subtlety over outright aggression and want daily comfort with weekend thrills.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Pure performance seekers wanting maximum power, those prioritizing fuel economy above all else, or drivers who need extensive rear seat space and cargo capacity.
editorial.buyers_summary: Look for well-maintained examples with service records, as these engines thrive on proper maintenance. The F Sport package is worth seeking out for its superior suspension tuning and aesthetic enhancements.
cons: Not as powerful as turbocharged competitors
